                            <h6 style="font-family: 'Overpass Mono', monospace;font-weight: bold;text-align: center;"><a onclick="javascript:ShowHide('eleven')">Third of March 2022</a></h6>
                            <div class="mid" id="eleven" style="display: none;">
                            <p style="font-family: 'Overpass Mono', monospace;text-align: center;">Bite Back!</p>
                            <p style="font-family: 'Overpass Mono', monospace;text-align: center;"><em> Day One: Editorial Writing cliniquing </a> . </em></p>
                            &nbsp;&nbsp;
                            <p style="font-family: 'Overpass Mono', monospace;text-align: left;"
                            <br>In prolonging the war between Ukraine, Russia is indirectly killing itself, starting from essential diplomatic roles up to the lives of the very citizens that it treasures. <br>
                            <br>
With a military multinational alliance recruiting countries all around its border, Russia opted to act on its anxiety and greed: it claimed that NATO’s expansion through Ukraine is unacceptable and distressed that Ukrainians are the ones acting against them, which they determined to be a plausible reason for war. As stated by the ABS-CBN News Channel, Russia’s invasion is centered around Kyiv, Ukraine’s capital, and with its end unforeseen, the war will be more harmful to their forces than beneficial. Using dirty tactics such as misinformation and propaganda will not make their situation better than ever.<br>
<br>
While Russia pushes through Ukraine’s defense, direct consequences hit the rest of its stubbornness to win the war. As stated by Richard Mills, United States deputy ambassador to UN, 12 Russian diplomats were expelled since they were taking part in activities not related to their current position that concerned their national security. Even the neutral Switzerland joins the EU-imposed sanctions to Russia. Major corporations like Shell, Aercap, Microsoft and Disney terminated some of their business involvements with the country. Leading sports coordinators agreed in banning Russian athletes in international events. As the Russian Ruble fell, the country’s decision to increase their interest rate to 20% troubled its citizens in doing so. These disadvantages are not worth it for their pursuit of power!<br>
<br>
While Russia faced indirect attacks coming from everywhere, Ukraine grasped on the receiving end of the world’s affection. Philippines’ Department of Foreign Affairs secretary Teodoro Locsin Jr. reached out to the ministers of the neighboring countries of Ukraine to receive Filipinos evacuating from Ukraine, even if they have no visa. The generosity of foreign individuals all around the world are helping the Ukrainians flee the bloodbath coming from their home country. What is Russia aiming for with all of the lives spilled from their greed?<br>
<br>
Russia’s choice to go to war is a decision that they will no longer have the chance to reverse. Ukraine’s measures to save itself and the world’s response on their plight is deserving on what it seems to be a prideful invasion. When the end is not in sight, Russia’s decision to invade Ukraine has bitten them back. It is up to them if they should let go or further fall back into the trap they have set for themselves.
